00:16:01.790 --> 00:16:02.540
And what is that?

00:16:02.540 --> 00:16:05.510
Well, that's a focus on
a specific improvement

00:16:05.510 --> 00:16:07.400
opportunity, as
we're going to have

00:16:07.400 --> 00:16:08.630
coming up here in a minute.

00:16:08.630 --> 00:16:12.050
It's an event that's
chartered by a sponsor

00:16:12.050 --> 00:16:14.990
in the organization, one
of the managements, who

00:16:14.990 --> 00:16:18.440
sets the goals, the what has to
be done, and the constraints,

00:16:18.440 --> 00:16:20.180
and provides the resources.

00:16:20.180 --> 00:16:21.198
And the resources are--

00:16:21.198 --> 00:16:22.490
we'll get to those in a minute.

00:16:22.490 --> 00:16:23.573
But they're mainly people.

00:16:23.573 --> 00:16:27.690
They provide coaches and
facilitators to help you.

00:16:27.690 --> 00:16:29.490
A rapid process
improvement workshop

00:16:29.490 --> 00:16:30.960
never goes over a week.

00:16:30.960 --> 00:16:34.140
Most of them are a week long.

00:16:34.140 --> 00:16:36.750
Sometimes they're less, if
it's a less complex problem.

00:16:36.750 --> 00:16:39.820
But it takes several months of
planning to get ready for this.

00:16:39.820 --> 00:16:42.600
And what it does is
it brings together,

00:16:42.600 --> 00:16:46.530
for the week, all the people
who need to interact to address

00:16:46.530 --> 00:16:48.690
this improvement opportunity.

00:16:48.690 --> 00:16:52.940
And the opposite of that
is that these people--

00:16:52.940 --> 00:16:56.340
the contrast would be that
these people are mainly

00:16:56.340 --> 00:16:58.500
doing their day jobs,
wherever they are,

00:16:58.500 --> 00:17:00.270
and you're trying to
do this improvement

00:17:00.270 --> 00:17:03.840
opportunity over a
distributed group of people

00:17:03.840 --> 00:17:05.460
in time and space.

00:17:05.460 --> 00:17:09.180
And what might take six months
to a year just to coordinate,

00:17:09.180 --> 00:17:11.265
you get done in one week.

00:17:11.265 --> 00:17:13.140
But in that week, that's
all these people do.

00:17:13.140 --> 00:17:15.210
They're released from all
their other activities,

00:17:15.210 --> 00:17:16.619
and they participate in this.

00:17:16.619 --> 00:17:18.732
And this is the kind
of thing that Sue does.

00:17:18.732 --> 00:17:20.190
I presume you run
these, don't you?

00:17:20.190 --> 00:17:20.670
AUDIENCE: Some of them.

00:17:20.670 --> 00:17:21.462
EARLL MURMAN: Yeah.

00:17:21.462 --> 00:17:22.619
Yeah.

00:17:22.619 --> 00:17:24.700
OK, so it involves
all the stakeholders.

00:17:24.700 --> 00:17:26.417
It's a very data-driven process.

00:17:26.417 --> 00:17:28.500
We've been trying to
emphasize you work with data.

00:17:28.500 --> 00:17:30.480
You get the value-stream data.

00:17:30.480 --> 00:17:35.010
The week ends with actually a
